Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the @rice{150%g}.

When boiling, add the rice and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pot. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{to taste} in a large pan on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @Irish Pork Sausages{225%g} and fry until browned, ~{7-8%minutes}, shifting as they colour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Drain and rinse the @Cannellini Beans{1%pack} in a sieve.

Add the @Chopped Tomato with Onion & Garlic{1%pack}, @paprika{1%sachet} and @dried thyme{1%sachet} to the pan. Simmer for ~{5-7%minutes}, until the sauce has reduced.

Add @water{100%ml} and cannellini beans.

Cook for an additional ~{4-5%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and @sugar{to taste}. Add a splash of @?water{} to loosen the sauce if required.

Toss the @salad leaves{40%g} with salt, pepper and a drizzle of oil.

Spoon fluffy rice into #bowls{} and top with the sausages and beans. Serve salad alongside.

Crumble @goat's cheese{100%g} over both salad and stew.

Finish all with a drizzle of oil and pepper.